result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody Daniel Carlson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cody Daniel Carlson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Cody Daniel Carlson was found guilty of Operate Vehicle w/o Consent-Passenger [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(4m).
  • Cody Daniel Carlson was found guilty of Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Eric Gordon Johnson, DF ATTY: John A. Kucinski, DF: Cody Daniel Carlson appeared.  Court called at 1:33 p.m.  Attorney Kucinski recites the agreement.    State amends Ct. 1 to a Misdemeanor Statute 943.23(4) Operation of a Vehicle as a Passenger w/o consent.  State amends Ct. 2 to a Misdemeanor Statute 943.50 Retail Theft.  C rt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads No Contest to the amended Ct 1 & the amended Ct 2.   Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds the DE adjudicated guilty of the amended Ct 1 & amended Ct. 2.  On motion of the State without objection, Crt dismisses Ct 3.   Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:  

Amended Ct. 1 & Amended Ct. 2 in 15CF575 to run concurrent to each other and to the Eau Claire County and Chippewa County Cases
- W/S 2 years probation with conditions
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- DE eligible to apply for expungement under Statute 973.015 after successful completion of probation
- Court costs totaling $443.00 for Ct. 1 & Ct. 2 to be paid through the DOC
- Credit for 60 days if revoked.
- DE to report for probation today 06/22/16
- DE's bail is continued until DE has signed up for probation and then is vacated
- 20 days to appeal
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 22, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
